41static bool CC_Sparc_Assign_SRet(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT,
42 MVT &LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
43 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State)
44{
45 assert (ArgFlags.isSRet());
46
47 // Assign SRet argument.
48 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomMem(ValNo, ValVT,
49 0,
50 LocVT, LocInfo));
51 return true;
52}
53
54static bool CC_Sparc_Assign_Split_64(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT,
55 MVT &LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
56 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State)
57{
58 static const MCPhysReg RegList[] = {
59 SP::I0, SP::I1, SP::I2, SP::I3, SP::I4, SP::I5
60 };
61 // Try to get first reg.
62 if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(RegList)) {
63 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
64 } else {
65 // Assign whole thing in stack.
66 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomMem(ValNo, ValVT,
67 State.AllocateStack(8,4),
68 LocVT, LocInfo));
69 return true;
70 }
71
72 // Try to get second reg.
73 if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(RegList))
74 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
75 else
76 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomMem(ValNo, ValVT,
77 State.AllocateStack(4,4),
78 LocVT, LocInfo));
79 return true;
80}

82static bool CC_Sparc_Assign_Ret_Split_64(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT,
83 MVT &LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
84 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State)
85{
86 static const MCPhysReg RegList[] = {
87 SP::I0, SP::I1, SP::I2, SP::I3, SP::I4, SP::I5
88 };
89
90 // Try to get first reg.
91 if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(RegList))
92 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
93 else
94 return false;
95
96 // Try to get second reg.
97 if (unsigned Reg = State.AllocateReg(RegList))
98 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
99 else
100 return false;
101
102 return true;
103}

105// Allocate a full-sized argument for the 64-bit ABI.
106static bool CC_Sparc64_Full(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT,
107 MVT &LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
108 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State) {
109 assert((LocVT == MVT::f32 || LocVT == MVT::f128
110 || LocVT.getSizeInBits() == 64) &&
111 "Can't handle non-64 bits locations");
112
113 // Stack space is allocated for all arguments starting from [%fp+BIAS+128].
114 unsigned size = (LocVT == MVT::f128) ? 16 : 8;
115 unsigned alignment = (LocVT == MVT::f128) ? 16 : 8;
116 unsigned Offset = State.AllocateStack(size, alignment);
117 unsigned Reg = 0;
118
119 if (LocVT == MVT::i64 && Offset < 6*8)
120 // Promote integers to %i0-%i5.
121 Reg = SP::I0 + Offset/8;
122 else if (LocVT == MVT::f64 && Offset < 16*8)
123 // Promote doubles to %d0-%d30. (Which LLVM calls D0-D15).
124 Reg = SP::D0 + Offset/8;
125 else if (LocVT == MVT::f32 && Offset < 16*8)
126 // Promote floats to %f1, %f3, ...
127 Reg = SP::F1 + Offset/4;
128 else if (LocVT == MVT::f128 && Offset < 16*8)
129 // Promote long doubles to %q0-%q28. (Which LLVM calls Q0-Q7).
130 Reg = SP::Q0 + Offset/16;
131
132 // Promote to register when possible, otherwise use the stack slot.
133 if (Reg) {
134 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
135 return true;
136 }
137
138 // This argument goes on the stack in an 8-byte slot.
139 // When passing floats, LocVT is smaller than 8 bytes. Adjust the offset to
140 // the right-aligned float. The first 4 bytes of the stack slot are undefined.
141 if (LocVT == MVT::f32)
142 Offset += 4;
143
144 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset, LocVT, LocInfo));
145 return true;
146}
147
148// Allocate a half-sized argument for the 64-bit ABI.
149//
150// This is used when passing { float, int } structs by value in registers.
151static bool CC_Sparc64_Half(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT,
152 MVT &LocVT, CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
153 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State) {
154 assert(LocVT.getSizeInBits() == 32 && "Can't handle non-32 bits locations");
155 unsigned Offset = State.AllocateStack(4, 4);
156
157 if (LocVT == MVT::f32 && Offset < 16*8) {
158 // Promote floats to %f0-%f31.
159 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, SP::F0 + Offset/4,
160 LocVT, LocInfo));
161 return true;
162 }
163
164 if (LocVT == MVT::i32 && Offset < 6*8) {
165 // Promote integers to %i0-%i5, using half the register.
166 unsigned Reg = SP::I0 + Offset/8;
167 LocVT = MVT::i64;
168 LocInfo = CCValAssign::AExt;
169
170 // Set the Custom bit if this i32 goes in the high bits of a register.
171 if (Offset % 8 == 0)
172 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getCustomReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg,
173 LocVT, LocInfo));
174 else
175 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getReg(ValNo, ValVT, Reg, LocVT, LocInfo));
176 return true;
177 }
178
179 State.addLoc(CCValAssign::getMem(ValNo, ValVT, Offset, LocVT, LocInfo));
180 return true;
181}

185// The calling conventions in SparcCallingConv.td are described in terms of the
186// callee's register window. This function translates registers to the
187// corresponding caller window %o register.
188static unsigned toCallerWindow(unsigned Reg) {
189 static_assert(SP::I0 + 7 == SP::I7 && SP::O0 + 7 == SP::O7,
190 "Unexpected enum");
191 if (Reg >= SP::I0 && Reg <= SP::I7)
192 return Reg - SP::I0 + SP::O0;
193 return Reg;
194}

196SDValue
197SparcTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
198 bool IsVarArg,
199 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
200 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
201 const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
202 if (Subtarget->is64Bit())
203 return LowerReturn_64(Chain, CallConv, IsVarArg, Outs, OutVals, DL, DAG);
204 return LowerReturn_32(Chain, CallConv, IsVarArg, Outs, OutVals, DL, DAG);
205}
206
207SDValue
208SparcTargetLowering::LowerReturn_32(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
209 bool IsVarArg,
210 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
211 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
212 const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
213 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
214
215 // CCValAssign - represent the assignment of the return value to locations.
216 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
217
218 // CCState - Info about the registers and stack slot.
219 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
220 *DAG.getContext());
221
222 // Analyze return values.
223 CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_Sparc32);
224
225 SDValue Flag;
226 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
227 // Make room for the return address offset.
228 RetOps.push_back(SDValue());
229
230 // Copy the result values into the output registers.
231 for (unsigned i = 0, realRVLocIdx = 0;
232 i != RVLocs.size();
233 ++i, ++realRVLocIdx) {
234 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
235 assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
236
237 SDValue Arg = OutVals[realRVLocIdx];
238
239 if (VA.needsCustom()) {
240 assert(VA.getLocVT() == MVT::v2i32);
241 // Legalize ret v2i32 -> ret 2 x i32 (Basically: do what would
242 // happen by default if this wasn't a legal type)
243
244 SDValue Part0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32,
245 Arg,
246 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
247 SDValue Part1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32,
248 Arg,
249 DAG.getConstant(1, DL, getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
250
251 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Part0, Flag);
252 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
253 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
254 VA = RVLocs[++i]; // skip ahead to next loc
255 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Part1,
256 Flag);
257 } else
258 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), Arg, Flag);
259
260 // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together with flags.
261 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
262 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
263 }
264
265 unsigned RetAddrOffset = 8; // Call Inst + Delay Slot
266 // If the function returns a struct, copy the SRetReturnReg to I0
267 if (MF.getFunction().hasStructRetAttr()) {
268 SparcMachineFunctionInfo *SFI = MF.getInfo<SparcMachineFunctionInfo>();
269 unsigned Reg = SFI->getSRetReturnReg();
270 if (!Reg)
271 llvm_unreachable("sret virtual register not created in the entry block");
272 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
273 SDValue Val = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, PtrVT);
274 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, SP::I0, Val, Flag);
275 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
276 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(SP::I0, PtrVT));
277 RetAddrOffset = 12; // CallInst + Delay Slot + Unimp
278 }
279
280 RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
281 RetOps[1] = DAG.getConstant(RetAddrOffset, DL, MVT::i32);
282
283 // Add the flag if we have it.
284 if (Flag.getNode())
285 RetOps.push_back(Flag);
286
287 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::RET_FLAG, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
288}

290// Lower return values for the 64-bit ABI.
291// Return values are passed the exactly the same way as function arguments.
292SDValue
293SparcTargetLowering::LowerReturn_64(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
294 bool IsVarArg,
295 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
296 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
297 const SDLoc &DL, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
298 // CCValAssign - represent the assignment of the return value to locations.
299 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
300
301 // CCState - Info about the registers and stack slot.
302 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
303 *DAG.getContext());
304
305 // Analyze return values.
306 CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_Sparc64);
307
308 SDValue Flag;
309 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
310
311 // The second operand on the return instruction is the return address offset.
312 // The return address is always %i7+8 with the 64-bit ABI.
313 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getConstant(8, DL, MVT::i32));
314
315 // Copy the result values into the output registers.
316 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
317 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
318 assert(VA.isRegLoc() && "Can only return in registers!");
319 SDValue OutVal = OutVals[i];
320
321 // Integer return values must be sign or zero extended by the callee.
322 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
323 case CCValAssign::Full: break;
324 case CCValAssign::SExt:
325 OutVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), OutVal);
326 break;
327 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
328 OutVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), OutVal);
329 break;
330 case CCValAssign::AExt:
331 OutVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), OutVal);
332 break;
333 default:
334 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
335 }
336
337 // The custom bit on an i32 return value indicates that it should be passed
338 // in the high bits of the register.
339 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.needsCustom()) {
340 OutVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, OutVal,
341 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
342
343 // The next value may go in the low bits of the same register.
344 // Handle both at once.
345 if (i+1 < RVLocs.size() && RVLocs[i+1].getLocReg() == VA.getLocReg()) {
346 SDValue NV = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64, OutVals[i+1]);
347 OutVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i64, OutVal, NV);
348 // Skip the next value, it's already done.
349 ++i;
350 }
351 }
352
353 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, VA.getLocReg(), OutVal, Flag);
354
355 // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together with flags.
356 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
357 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
358 }
359
360 RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
361
362 // Add the flag if we have it.
363 if (Flag.getNode())
364 RetOps.push_back(Flag);
365
366 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::RET_FLAG, DL, MVT::Other, RetOps);
367}

369SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
370 SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
371 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
372 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
373 if (Subtarget->is64Bit())
374 return LowerFormalArguments_64(Chain, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins,
375 DL, DAG, InVals);
376 return LowerFormalArguments_32(Chain, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins,
377 DL, DAG, InVals);
378}
379
380/// LowerFormalArguments32 - V8 uses a very simple ABI, where all values are
381/// passed in either one or two GPRs, including FP values. TODO: we should
382/// pass FP values in FP registers for fastcc functions.
383SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments_32(
384 SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool isVarArg,
385 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &dl,
386 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
387 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
388 MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MF.getRegInfo();
389 SparcMachineFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<SparcMachineFunctionInfo>();
390
391 // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
392 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
393 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, isVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs,
394 *DAG.getContext());
395 CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_Sparc32);
396
397 const unsigned StackOffset = 92;
398 bool IsLittleEndian = DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian();
399
400 unsigned InIdx = 0;
401 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i, ++InIdx) {
402 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
403
404 if (Ins[InIdx].Flags.isSRet()) {
405 if (InIdx != 0)
406 report_fatal_error("sparc only supports sret on the first parameter");
407 // Get SRet from [%fp+64].
408 int FrameIdx = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(4, 64, true);
409 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FrameIdx, MVT::i32);
410 SDValue Arg =
411 DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, dl, Chain, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
412 InVals.push_back(Arg);
413 continue;
414 }
415
416 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
417 if (VA.needsCustom()) {
418 assert(VA.getLocVT() == MVT::f64 || VA.getLocVT() == MVT::v2i32);
419
420 unsigned VRegHi = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&SP::IntRegsRegClass);
421 MF.getRegInfo().addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), VRegHi);
422 SDValue HiVal = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, VRegHi, MVT::i32);
423
424 assert(i+1 < e);
425 CCValAssign &NextVA = ArgLocs[++i];
426
427 SDValue LoVal;
428 if (NextVA.isMemLoc()) {
429 int FrameIdx = MF.getFrameInfo().
430 CreateFixedObject(4, StackOffset+NextVA.getLocMemOffset(),true);
431 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FrameIdx, MVT::i32);
432 LoVal = DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, dl, Chain, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
433 } else {
434 unsigned loReg = MF.addLiveIn(NextVA.getLocReg(),
435 &SP::IntRegsRegClass);
436 LoVal = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, loReg, MVT::i32);
437 }
438
439 if (IsLittleEndian)
440 std::swap(LoVal, HiVal);
441
442 SDValue WholeValue =
443 DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, MVT::i64, LoVal, HiVal);
444 WholeValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VA.getLocVT(), WholeValue);
445 InVals.push_back(WholeValue);
446 continue;
447 }
448 unsigned VReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&SP::IntRegsRegClass);
449 MF.getRegInfo().addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), VReg);
450 SDValue Arg = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, VReg, MVT::i32);
451 if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::f32)
452 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::f32, Arg);
453 else if (VA.getLocVT() != MVT::i32) {
454 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, dl, MVT::i32, Arg,
455 DAG.getValueType(VA.getLocVT()));
456 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
457 }
458 InVals.push_back(Arg);
459 continue;
460 }
461
462 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
463
464 unsigned Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset()+StackOffset;
465 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
466
467 if (VA.needsCustom()) {
468 assert(VA.getValVT() == MVT::f64 || VA.getValVT() == MVT::v2i32);
469 // If it is double-word aligned, just load.
470 if (Offset % 8 == 0) {
471 int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(8,
472 Offset,
473 true);
474 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
475 SDValue Load =
476 DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), dl, Chain, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
477 InVals.push_back(Load);
478 continue;
479 }
480
481 int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(4,
482 Offset,
483 true);
484 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
485 SDValue HiVal =
486 DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, dl, Chain, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
487 int FI2 = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(4,
488 Offset+4,
489 true);
490 SDValue FIPtr2 = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI2, PtrVT);
491
492 SDValue LoVal =
493 DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, dl, Chain, FIPtr2, MachinePointerInfo());
494
495 if (IsLittleEndian)
496 std::swap(LoVal, HiVal);
497
498 SDValue WholeValue =
499 DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, MVT::i64, LoVal, HiVal);
500 WholeValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VA.getValVT(), WholeValue);
501 InVals.push_back(WholeValue);
502 continue;
503 }
504
505 int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(4,
506 Offset,
507 true);
508 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT);
509 SDValue Load ;
510 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i32 || VA.getValVT() == MVT::f32) {
511 Load = DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), dl, Chain, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
512 } else if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::f128) {
513 report_fatal_error("SPARCv8 does not handle f128 in calls; "
514 "pass indirectly");
515 } else {
516 // We shouldn't see any other value types here.
517 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected ValVT encountered in frame lowering.");
518 }
519 InVals.push_back(Load);
520 }
521
522 if (MF.getFunction().hasStructRetAttr()) {
523 // Copy the SRet Argument to SRetReturnReg.
524 SparcMachineFunctionInfo *SFI = MF.getInfo<SparcMachineFunctionInfo>();
525 unsigned Reg = SFI->getSRetReturnReg();
526 if (!Reg) {
527 Reg = MF.getRegInfo().createVirtualRegister(&SP::IntRegsRegClass);
528 SFI->setSRetReturnReg(Reg);
529 }
530 SDValue Copy = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Reg, InVals[0]);
531 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Copy, Chain);
532 }
533
534 // Store remaining ArgRegs to the stack if this is a varargs function.
535 if (isVarArg) {
536 static const MCPhysReg ArgRegs[] = {
537 SP::I0, SP::I1, SP::I2, SP::I3, SP::I4, SP::I5
538 };
539 unsigned NumAllocated = CCInfo.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs);
540 const MCPhysReg *CurArgReg = ArgRegs+NumAllocated, *ArgRegEnd = ArgRegs+6;
541 unsigned ArgOffset = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
542 if (NumAllocated == 6)
543 ArgOffset += StackOffset;
544 else {
545 assert(!ArgOffset);
546 ArgOffset = 68+4*NumAllocated;
547 }
548
549 // Remember the vararg offset for the va_start implementation.
550 FuncInfo->setVarArgsFrameOffset(ArgOffset);
551
552 std::vector<SDValue> OutChains;
553
554 for (; CurArgReg != ArgRegEnd; ++CurArgReg) {
555 unsigned VReg = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&SP::IntRegsRegClass);
556 MF.getRegInfo().addLiveIn(*CurArgReg, VReg);
557 SDValue Arg = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getRoot(), dl, VReg, MVT::i32);
558
559 int FrameIdx = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(4, ArgOffset,
560 true);
561 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FrameIdx, MVT::i32);
562
563 OutChains.push_back(
564 DAG.getStore(DAG.getRoot(), dl, Arg, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo()));
565 ArgOffset += 4;
566 }
567
568 if (!OutChains.empty()) {
569 OutChains.push_back(Chain);
570 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OutChains);
571 }
572 }
573
574 return Chain;
575}

577// Lower formal arguments for the 64 bit ABI.
578SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments_64(
579 SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
580 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &DL,
581 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
582 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
583
584 // Analyze arguments according to CC_Sparc64.
585 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
586 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs,
587 *DAG.getContext());
588 CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_Sparc64);
589
590 // The argument array begins at %fp+BIAS+128, after the register save area.
591 const unsigned ArgArea = 128;
592
593 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
594 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
595 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
596 // This argument is passed in a register.
597 // All integer register arguments are promoted by the caller to i64.
598
599 // Create a virtual register for the promoted live-in value.
600 unsigned VReg = MF.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(),
601 getRegClassFor(VA.getLocVT()));
602 SDValue Arg = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VReg, VA.getLocVT());
603
604 // Get the high bits for i32 struct elements.
605 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.needsCustom())
606 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg,
607 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
608
609 // The caller promoted the argument, so insert an Assert?ext SDNode so we
610 // won't promote the value again in this function.
611 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
612 case CCValAssign::SExt:
613 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg,
614 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
615 break;
616 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
617 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg,
618 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
619 break;
620 default:
621 break;
622 }
623
624 // Truncate the register down to the argument type.
625 if (VA.isExtInLoc())
626 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), Arg);
627
628 InVals.push_back(Arg);
629 continue;
630 }
631
632 // The registers are exhausted. This argument was passed on the stack.
633 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
634 // The CC_Sparc64_Full/Half functions compute stack offsets relative to the
635 // beginning of the arguments area at %fp+BIAS+128.
636 unsigned Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset() + ArgArea;
637 unsigned ValSize = VA.getValVT().getSizeInBits() / 8;
638 // Adjust offset for extended arguments, SPARC is big-endian.
639 // The caller will have written the full slot with extended bytes, but we
640 // prefer our own extending loads.
641 if (VA.isExtInLoc())
642 Offset += 8 - ValSize;
643 int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(ValSize, Offset, true);
644 InVals.push_back(
645 DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), DL, Chain,
646 DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout())),
647 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
648 }
649
650 if (!IsVarArg)
651 return Chain;
652
653 // This function takes variable arguments, some of which may have been passed
654 // in registers %i0-%i5. Variable floating point arguments are never passed
655 // in floating point registers. They go on %i0-%i5 or on the stack like
656 // integer arguments.
657 //
658 // The va_start intrinsic needs to know the offset to the first variable
659 // argument.
660 unsigned ArgOffset = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
661 SparcMachineFunctionInfo *FuncInfo = MF.getInfo<SparcMachineFunctionInfo>();
662 // Skip the 128 bytes of register save area.
663 FuncInfo->setVarArgsFrameOffset(ArgOffset + ArgArea +
664 Subtarget->getStackPointerBias());
665
666 // Save the variable arguments that were passed in registers.
667 // The caller is required to reserve stack space for 6 arguments regardless
668 // of how many arguments were actually passed.
669 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> OutChains;
670 for (; ArgOffset < 6*8; ArgOffset += 8) {
671 unsigned VReg = MF.addLiveIn(SP::I0 + ArgOffset/8, &SP::I64RegsRegClass);
672 SDValue VArg = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, VReg, MVT::i64);
673 int FI = MF.getFrameInfo().CreateFixedObject(8, ArgOffset + ArgArea, true);
674 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout());
675 OutChains.push_back(
676 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, VArg, DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, PtrVT),
677 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI)));
678 }
679
680 if (!OutChains.empty())
681 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, OutChains);
682
683 return Chain;
684}
685
686SDValue
687SparcTargetLowering::LowerCall(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
688 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
689 if (Subtarget->is64Bit())
690 return LowerCall_64(CLI, InVals);
691 return LowerCall_32(CLI, InVals);
692}
693
694static bool hasReturnsTwiceAttr(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Callee,
695 ImmutableCallSite CS) {
696 if (CS)
697 return CS.hasFnAttr(Attribute::ReturnsTwice);
698
699 const Function *CalleeFn = nullptr;
700 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
701 CalleeFn = dyn_cast<Function>(G->getGlobal());
702 } else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *E =
703 dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
704 const Function &Fn = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
705 const Module *M = Fn.getParent();
706 const char *CalleeName = E->getSymbol();
707 CalleeFn = M->getFunction(CalleeName);
708 }
709
710 if (!CalleeFn)
711 return false;
712 return CalleeFn->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReturnsTwice);
713}
714
715// Lower a call for the 32-bit ABI.
716SDValue
717SparcTargetLowering::LowerCall_32(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
718 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
719 SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
720 SDLoc &dl = CLI.DL;
721 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
722 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
723 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
724 SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
725 SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
726 bool &isTailCall = CLI.IsTailCall;
727 CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
728 bool isVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
729
730 // Sparc target does not yet support tail call optimization.
731 isTailCall = false;
732
733 // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
734 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
735 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, isVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs,
736 *DAG.getContext());
737 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_Sparc32);
738
739 // Get the size of the outgoing arguments stack space requirement.
740 unsigned ArgsSize = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
741
742 // Keep stack frames 8-byte aligned.
743 ArgsSize = (ArgsSize+7) & ~7;
744
745 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
746
747 // Create local copies for byval args.
748 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ByValArgs;
749 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Outs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
750 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
751 if (!Flags.isByVal())
752 continue;
753
754 SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
755 unsigned Size = Flags.getByValSize();
756 unsigned Align = Flags.getByValAlign();
757
758 if (Size > 0U) {
759 int FI = MFI.CreateStackObject(Size, Align, false);
760 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
761 SDValue SizeNode = DAG.getConstant(Size, dl, MVT::i32);
762
763 Chain = DAG.getMemcpy(Chain, dl, FIPtr, Arg, SizeNode, Align,
764 false, // isVolatile,
765 (Size <= 32), // AlwaysInline if size <= 32,
766 false, // isTailCall
767 /*MustPreserveCheriCapabilities=*/false,
768 MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
769 ByValArgs.push_back(FIPtr);
770 }
771 else {
772 SDValue nullVal;
773 ByValArgs.push_back(nullVal);
774 }
775 }
776
777 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, ArgsSize, 0, dl);
778
779 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>, 8> RegsToPass;
780 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
781
782 const unsigned StackOffset = 92;
783 bool hasStructRetAttr = false;
784 unsigned SRetArgSize = 0;
785 // Walk the register/memloc assignments, inserting copies/loads.
786 for (unsigned i = 0, realArgIdx = 0, byvalArgIdx = 0, e = ArgLocs.size();
787 i != e;
788 ++i, ++realArgIdx) {
789 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
790 SDValue Arg = OutVals[realArgIdx];
791
792 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[realArgIdx].Flags;
793
794 // Use local copy if it is a byval arg.
795 if (Flags.isByVal()) {
796 Arg = ByValArgs[byvalArgIdx++];
797 if (!Arg) {
798 continue;
799 }
800 }
801
802 // Promote the value if needed.
803 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
804 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
805 case CCValAssign::Full: break;
806 case CCValAssign::SExt:
807 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
808 break;
809 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
810 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
811 break;
812 case CCValAssign::AExt:
813 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
814 break;
815 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
816 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
817 break;
818 }
819
820 if (Flags.isSRet()) {
821 assert(VA.needsCustom());
822 // store SRet argument in %sp+64
823 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, MVT::i32);
824 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(64, dl);
825 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
826 MemOpChains.push_back(
827 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Arg, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
828 hasStructRetAttr = true;
829 // sret only allowed on first argument
830 assert(Outs[realArgIdx].OrigArgIndex == 0);
831 PointerType *Ty = cast<PointerType>(CLI.getArgs()[0].Ty);
832 Type *ElementTy = Ty->getElementType();
833 SRetArgSize = DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(ElementTy);
834 continue;
835 }
836
837 if (VA.needsCustom()) {
838 assert(VA.getLocVT() == MVT::f64 || VA.getLocVT() == MVT::v2i32);
839
840 if (VA.isMemLoc()) {
841 unsigned Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset() + StackOffset;
842 // if it is double-word aligned, just store.
843 if (Offset % 8 == 0) {
844 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, MVT::i32);
845 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset, dl);
846 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
847 MemOpChains.push_back(
848 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Arg, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
849 continue;
850 }
851 }
852
853 if (VA.getLocVT() == MVT::f64) {
854 // Move from the float value from float registers into the
855 // integer registers.
856 if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Arg))
857 Arg = bitcastConstantFPToInt(C, dl, DAG);
858 else
859 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::v2i32, Arg);
860 }
861
862 SDValue Part0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, MVT::i32,
863 Arg,
864 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
865 SDValue Part1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, MVT::i32,
866 Arg,
867 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
868
869 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
870 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Part0));
871 assert(i+1 != e);
872 CCValAssign &NextVA = ArgLocs[++i];
873 if (NextVA.isRegLoc()) {
874 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(NextVA.getLocReg(), Part1));
875 } else {
876 // Store the second part in stack.
877 unsigned Offset = NextVA.getLocMemOffset() + StackOffset;
878 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, MVT::i32);
879 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset, dl);
880 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
881 MemOpChains.push_back(
882 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Part1, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
883 }
884 } else {
885 unsigned Offset = VA.getLocMemOffset() + StackOffset;
886 // Store the first part.
887 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, MVT::i32);
888 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset, dl);
889 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
890 MemOpChains.push_back(
891 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Part0, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
892 // Store the second part.
893 PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(Offset + 4, dl);
894 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
895 MemOpChains.push_back(
896 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Part1, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
897 }
898 continue;
899 }
900
901 // Arguments that can be passed on register must be kept at
902 // RegsToPass vector
903 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
904 if (VA.getLocVT() != MVT::f32) {
905 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg));
906 continue;
907 }
908 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::i32, Arg);
909 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg));
910 continue;
911 }
912
913 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
914
915 // Create a store off the stack pointer for this argument.
916 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, MVT::i32);
917 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset() + StackOffset,
918 dl);
919 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, PtrOff);
920 MemOpChains.push_back(
921 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Arg, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
922 }
923
924
925 // Emit all stores, make sure the occur before any copies into physregs.
926 if (!MemOpChains.empty())
927 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
928
929 // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes chained together with token
930 // chain and flag operands which copy the outgoing args into registers.
931 // The InFlag in necessary since all emitted instructions must be
932 // stuck together.
933 SDValue InFlag;
934 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
935 unsigned Reg = toCallerWindow(RegsToPass[i].first);
936 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, Reg, RegsToPass[i].second, InFlag);
937 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
938 }
939
940 bool hasReturnsTwice = hasReturnsTwiceAttr(DAG, Callee, CLI.CS);
941
942 // If the callee is a GlobalAddress node (quite common, every direct call is)
943 // turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress node so that legalize doesn't hack it.
944 // Likewise ExternalSymbol -> TargetExternalSymbol.
945 unsigned TF = isPositionIndependent() ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_WPLT30 : 0;
946 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee))
947 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(G->getGlobal(), dl, MVT::i32, 0, TF);
948 else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *E = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee))
949 Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalFunctionSymbol(E->getSymbol(), TF);
950
951 // Returns a chain & a flag for retval copy to use
952 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
953 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
954 Ops.push_back(Chain);
955 Ops.push_back(Callee);
956 if (hasStructRetAttr)
957 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(SRetArgSize, dl, MVT::i32));
958 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i)
959 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(toCallerWindow(RegsToPass[i].first),
960 RegsToPass[i].second.getValueType()));
961
962 // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
963 const SparcRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
964 const uint32_t *Mask =
965 ((hasReturnsTwice)
966 ? TRI->getRTCallPreservedMask(CallConv)
967 : TRI->getCallPreservedMask(DAG.getMachineFunction(), CallConv));
968 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
969 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
970
971 if (InFlag.getNode())
972 Ops.push_back(InFlag);
973
974 Chain = DAG.getNode(SPISD::CALL, dl, NodeTys, Ops);
975 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
976
977 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(ArgsSize, dl, true),
978 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, true), InFlag, dl);
979 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
980
981 // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
982 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
983 CCState RVInfo(CallConv, isVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
984 *DAG.getContext());
985
986 RVInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_Sparc32);
987
988 // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
989 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
990 if (RVLocs[i].getLocVT() == MVT::v2i32) {
991 SDValue Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::UNDEF, dl, MVT::v2i32);
992 SDValue Lo = DAG.getCopyFromReg(
993 Chain, dl, toCallerWindow(RVLocs[i++].getLocReg()), MVT::i32, InFlag);
994 Chain = Lo.getValue(1);
995 InFlag = Lo.getValue(2);
996 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, MVT::v2i32, Vec, Lo,
997 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, MVT::i32));
998 SDValue Hi = DAG.getCopyFromReg(
999 Chain, dl, toCallerWindow(RVLocs[i].getLocReg()), MVT::i32, InFlag);
1000 Chain = Hi.getValue(1);
1001 InFlag = Hi.getValue(2);
1002 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, MVT::v2i32, Vec, Hi,
1003 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, MVT::i32));
1004 InVals.push_back(Vec);
1005 } else {
1006 Chain =
1007 DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, toCallerWindow(RVLocs[i].getLocReg()),
1008 RVLocs[i].getValVT(), InFlag)
1009 .getValue(1);
1010 InFlag = Chain.getValue(2);
1011 InVals.push_back(Chain.getValue(0));
1012 }
1013 }
1014
1015 return Chain;
1016}

1018// FIXME? Maybe this could be a TableGen attribute on some registers and
1019// this table could be generated automatically from RegInfo.
1020unsigned SparcTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char* RegName, EVT VT,
1021 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1022 unsigned Reg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(RegName)
1023 .Case("i0", SP::I0).Case("i1", SP::I1).Case("i2", SP::I2).Case("i3", SP::I3)
1024 .Case("i4", SP::I4).Case("i5", SP::I5).Case("i6", SP::I6).Case("i7", SP::I7)
1025 .Case("o0", SP::O0).Case("o1", SP::O1).Case("o2", SP::O2).Case("o3", SP::O3)
1026 .Case("o4", SP::O4).Case("o5", SP::O5).Case("o6", SP::O6).Case("o7", SP::O7)
1027 .Case("l0", SP::L0).Case("l1", SP::L1).Case("l2", SP::L2).Case("l3", SP::L3)
1028 .Case("l4", SP::L4).Case("l5", SP::L5).Case("l6", SP::L6).Case("l7", SP::L7)
1029 .Case("g0", SP::G0).Case("g1", SP::G1).Case("g2", SP::G2).Case("g3", SP::G3)
1030 .Case("g4", SP::G4).Case("g5", SP::G5).Case("g6", SP::G6).Case("g7", SP::G7)
1031 .Default(0);
1032
1033 if (Reg)
1034 return Reg;
1035
1036 report_fatal_error("Invalid register name global variable");
1037}
1038
1039// Fixup floating point arguments in the ... part of a varargs call.
1040//
1041// The SPARC v9 ABI requires that floating point arguments are treated the same
1042// as integers when calling a varargs function. This does not apply to the
1043// fixed arguments that are part of the function's prototype.
1044//
1045// This function post-processes a CCValAssign array created by
1046// AnalyzeCallOperands().
1047static void fixupVariableFloatArgs(SmallVectorImpl<CCValAssign> &ArgLocs,
1048 ArrayRef<ISD::OutputArg> Outs) {
1049 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1050 const CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
1051 MVT ValTy = VA.getLocVT();
1052 // FIXME: What about f32 arguments? C promotes them to f64 when calling
1053 // varargs functions.
1054 if (!VA.isRegLoc() || (ValTy != MVT::f64 && ValTy != MVT::f128))
1055 continue;
1056 // The fixed arguments to a varargs function still go in FP registers.
1057 if (Outs[VA.getValNo()].IsFixed)
1058 continue;
1059
1060 // This floating point argument should be reassigned.
1061 CCValAssign NewVA;
1062
1063 // Determine the offset into the argument array.
1064 unsigned firstReg = (ValTy == MVT::f64) ? SP::D0 : SP::Q0;
1065 unsigned argSize = (ValTy == MVT::f64) ? 8 : 16;
1066 unsigned Offset = argSize * (VA.getLocReg() - firstReg);
1067 assert(Offset < 16*8 && "Offset out of range, bad register enum?");
1068
1069 if (Offset < 6*8) {
1070 // This argument should go in %i0-%i5.
1071 unsigned IReg = SP::I0 + Offset/8;
1072 if (ValTy == MVT::f64)
1073 // Full register, just bitconvert into i64.
1074 NewVA = CCValAssign::getReg(VA.getValNo(), VA.getValVT(),
1075 IReg, MVT::i64, CCValAssign::BCvt);
1076 else {
1077 assert(ValTy == MVT::f128 && "Unexpected type!");
1078 // Full register, just bitconvert into i128 -- We will lower this into
1079 // two i64s in LowerCall_64.
1080 NewVA = CCValAssign::getCustomReg(VA.getValNo(), VA.getValVT(),
1081 IReg, MVT::i128, CCValAssign::BCvt);
1082 }
1083 } else {
1084 // This needs to go to memory, we're out of integer registers.
1085 NewVA = CCValAssign::getMem(VA.getValNo(), VA.getValVT(),
1086 Offset, VA.getLocVT(), VA.getLocInfo());
1087 }
1088 ArgLocs[i] = NewVA;
1089 }
1090}
1091
1092// Lower a call for the 64-bit ABI.
1093SDValue
1094SparcTargetLowering::LowerCall_64(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
1095 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
1096 SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
1097 SDLoc DL = CLI.DL;
1098 SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
1099 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1100
1101 // Sparc target does not yet support tail call optimization.
1102 CLI.IsTailCall = false;
1103
1104 // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
1105 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
1106 CCState CCInfo(CLI.CallConv, CLI.IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), ArgLocs,
1107 *DAG.getContext());
1108 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(CLI.Outs, CC_Sparc64);
1109
1110 // Get the size of the outgoing arguments stack space requirement.
1111 // The stack offset computed by CC_Sparc64 includes all arguments.
1112 // Called functions expect 6 argument words to exist in the stack frame, used
1113 // or not.
1114 unsigned ArgsSize = std::max(6*8u, CCInfo.getNextStackOffset());
1115
1116 // Keep stack frames 16-byte aligned.
1117 ArgsSize = alignTo(ArgsSize, 16);
1118
1119 // Varargs calls require special treatment.
1120 if (CLI.IsVarArg)
1121 fixupVariableFloatArgs(ArgLocs, CLI.Outs);
1122
1123 // Adjust the stack pointer to make room for the arguments.
1124 // FIXME: Use hasReservedCallFrame to avoid %sp adjustments around all calls
1125 // with more than 6 arguments.
1126 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, ArgsSize, 0, DL);
1127
1128 // Collect the set of registers to pass to the function and their values.
1129 // This will be emitted as a sequence of CopyToReg nodes glued to the call
1130 // instruction.
1131 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>, 8> RegsToPass;
1132
1133 // Collect chains from all the memory opeations that copy arguments to the
1134 // stack. They must follow the stack pointer adjustment above and precede the
1135 // call instruction itself.
1136 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
1137
1138 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1139 const CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
1140 SDValue Arg = CLI.OutVals[i];
1141
1142 // Promote the value if needed.
1143 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
1144 default:
1145 llvm_unreachable("Unknown location info!");
1146 case CCValAssign::Full:
1147 break;
1148 case CCValAssign::SExt:
1149 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
1150 break;
1151 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
1152 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
1153 break;
1154 case CCValAssign::AExt:
1155 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
1156 break;
1157 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
1158 // fixupVariableFloatArgs() may create bitcasts from f128 to i128. But
1159 // SPARC does not support i128 natively. Lower it into two i64, see below.
1160 if (!VA.needsCustom() || VA.getValVT() != MVT::f128
1161 || VA.getLocVT() != MVT::i128)
1162 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
1163 break;
1164 }
1165
1166 if (VA.isRegLoc()) {
1167 if (VA.needsCustom() && VA.getValVT() == MVT::f128
1168 && VA.getLocVT() == MVT::i128) {
1169 // Store and reload into the integer register reg and reg+1.
1170 unsigned Offset = 8 * (VA.getLocReg() - SP::I0);
1171 unsigned StackOffset = Offset + Subtarget->getStackPointerBias() + 128;
1172 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, PtrVT);
1173 SDValue HiPtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(StackOffset, DL);
1174 HiPtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr, HiPtrOff);
1175 SDValue LoPtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(StackOffset + 8, DL);
1176 LoPtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr, LoPtrOff);
1177
1178 // Store to %sp+BIAS+128+Offset
1179 SDValue Store =
1180 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Arg, HiPtrOff, MachinePointerInfo());
1181 // Load into Reg and Reg+1
1182 SDValue Hi64 =
1183 DAG.getLoad(MVT::i64, DL, Store, HiPtrOff, MachinePointerInfo());
1184 SDValue Lo64 =
1185 DAG.getLoad(MVT::i64, DL, Store, LoPtrOff, MachinePointerInfo());
1186 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(toCallerWindow(VA.getLocReg()),
1187 Hi64));
1188 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(toCallerWindow(VA.getLocReg()+1),
1189 Lo64));
1190 continue;
1191 }
1192
1193 // The custom bit on an i32 return value indicates that it should be
1194 // passed in the high bits of the register.
1195 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.needsCustom()) {
1196 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, MVT::i64, Arg,
1197 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
1198
1199 // The next value may go in the low bits of the same register.
1200 // Handle both at once.
1201 if (i+1 < ArgLocs.size() && ArgLocs[i+1].isRegLoc() &&
1202 ArgLocs[i+1].getLocReg() == VA.getLocReg()) {
1203 SDValue NV = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i64,
1204 CLI.OutVals[i+1]);
1205 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MVT::i64, Arg, NV);
1206 // Skip the next value, it's already done.
1207 ++i;
1208 }
1209 }
1210 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(toCallerWindow(VA.getLocReg()), Arg));
1211 continue;
1212 }
1213
1214 assert(VA.isMemLoc());
1215
1216 // Create a store off the stack pointer for this argument.
1217 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.getRegister(SP::O6, PtrVT);
1218 // The argument area starts at %fp+BIAS+128 in the callee frame,
1219 // %sp+BIAS+128 in ours.
1220 SDValue PtrOff = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(VA.getLocMemOffset() +
1221 Subtarget->getStackPointerBias() +
1222 128, DL);
1223 PtrOff = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr, PtrOff);
1224 MemOpChains.push_back(
1225 DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Arg, PtrOff, MachinePointerInfo()));
1226 }
1227
1228 // Emit all stores, make sure they occur before the call.
1229 if (!MemOpChains.empty())
1230 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
1231
1232 // Build a sequence of CopyToReg nodes glued together with token chain and
1233 // glue operands which copy the outgoing args into registers. The InGlue is
1234 // necessary since all emitted instructions must be stuck together in order
1235 // to pass the live physical registers.
1236 SDValue InGlue;
1237 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1238 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL,
1239 RegsToPass[i].first, RegsToPass[i].second, InGlue);
1240 InGlue = Chain.getValue(1);
1241 }
1242
1243 // If the callee is a GlobalAddress node (quite common, every direct call is)
1244 // turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress node so that legalize doesn't hack it.
1245 // Likewise ExternalSymbol -> TargetExternalSymbol.
1246 SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
1247 bool hasReturnsTwice = hasReturnsTwiceAttr(DAG, Callee, CLI.CS);
1248 unsigned TF = isPositionIndependent() ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_WPLT30 : 0;
1249 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee))
1250 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(G->getGlobal(), DL, PtrVT, 0, TF);
1251 else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *E = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee))
1252 Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalFunctionSymbol(E->getSymbol(), TF);
1253
1254 // Build the operands for the call instruction itself.
1255 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
1256 Ops.push_back(Chain);
1257 Ops.push_back(Callee);
1258 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i)
1259 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegsToPass[i].first,
1260 RegsToPass[i].second.getValueType()));
1261
1262 // Add a register mask operand representing the call-preserved registers.
1263 const SparcRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
1264 const uint32_t *Mask =
1265 ((hasReturnsTwice) ? TRI->getRTCallPreservedMask(CLI.CallConv)
1266 : TRI->getCallPreservedMask(DAG.getMachineFunction(),
1267 CLI.CallConv));
1268 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
1269 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
1270
1271 // Make sure the CopyToReg nodes are glued to the call instruction which
1272 // consumes the registers.
1273 if (InGlue.getNode())
1274 Ops.push_back(InGlue);
1275
1276 // Now the call itself.
1277 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
1278 Chain = DAG.getNode(SPISD::CALL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
1279 InGlue = Chain.getValue(1);
1280
1281 // Revert the stack pointer immediately after the call.
1282 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(ArgsSize, DL, true),
1283 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL, true), InGlue, DL);
1284 InGlue = Chain.getValue(1);
1285
1286 // Now extract the return values. This is more or less the same as
1287 // LowerFormalArguments_64.
1288
1289 // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
1290 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
1291 CCState RVInfo(CLI.CallConv, CLI.IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
1292 *DAG.getContext());
1293
1294 // Set inreg flag manually for codegen generated library calls that
1295 // return float.
1296 if (CLI.Ins.size() == 1 && CLI.Ins[0].VT == MVT::f32 && !CLI.CS)
1297 CLI.Ins[0].Flags.setInReg();
1298
1299 RVInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(CLI.Ins, RetCC_Sparc64);
1300
1301 // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
1302 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
1303 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
1304 unsigned Reg = toCallerWindow(VA.getLocReg());
1305
1306 // When returning 'inreg {i32, i32 }', two consecutive i32 arguments can
1307 // reside in the same register in the high and low bits. Reuse the
1308 // CopyFromReg previous node to avoid duplicate copies.
1309 SDValue RV;
1310 if (RegisterSDNode *SrcReg = dyn_cast<RegisterSDNode>(Chain.getOperand(1)))
1311 if (SrcReg->getReg() == Reg && Chain->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg)
1312 RV = Chain.getValue(0);
1313
1314 // But usually we'll create a new CopyFromReg for a different register.
1315 if (!RV.getNode()) {
1316 RV = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, Reg, RVLocs[i].getLocVT(), InGlue);
1317 Chain = RV.getValue(1);
1318 InGlue = Chain.getValue(2);
1319 }
1320
1321 // Get the high bits for i32 struct elements.
1322 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i32 && VA.needsCustom())
1323 RV = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VA.getLocVT(), RV,
1324 DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
1325
1326 // The callee promoted the return value, so insert an Assert?ext SDNode so
1327 // we won't promote the value again in this function.
1328 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
1329 case CCValAssign::SExt:
1330 RV = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), RV,
1331 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
1332 break;
1333 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
1334 RV = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, DL, VA.getLocVT(), RV,
1335 DAG.getValueType(VA.getValVT()));
1336 break;
1337 default:
1338 break;
1339 }
1340
1341 // Truncate the register down to the return value type.
1342 if (VA.isExtInLoc())
1343 RV = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VA.getValVT(), RV);
1344
1345 InVals.push_back(RV);
1346 }
1347
1348 return Chain;
1349}

1354
1355TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind SparcTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(AtomicRMWInst *AI) const {
1356 if (AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::Xchg &&
1357 AI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 32)
1358 return AtomicExpansionKind::None; // Uses xchg instruction
1359
1360 return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
1361}

1363/// IntCondCCodeToICC - Convert a DAG integer condition code to a SPARC ICC
1364/// condition.
1365static SPCC::CondCodes IntCondCCodeToICC(ISD::CondCode CC) {
1366 switch (CC) {
1367 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer condition code!");
1368 case ISD::SETEQ: return SPCC::ICC_E;
1369 case ISD::SETNE: return SPCC::ICC_NE;
1370 case ISD::SETLT: return SPCC::ICC_L;
1371 case ISD::SETGT: return SPCC::ICC_G;
1372 case ISD::SETLE: return SPCC::ICC_LE;
1373 case ISD::SETGE: return SPCC::ICC_GE;
1374 case ISD::SETULT: return SPCC::ICC_CS;
1375 case ISD::SETULE: return SPCC::ICC_LEU;
1376 case ISD::SETUGT: return SPCC::ICC_GU;
1377 case ISD::SETUGE: return SPCC::ICC_CC;
1378 }
1379}
1380
1381/// FPCondCCodeToFCC - Convert a DAG floatingp oint condition code to a SPARC
1382/// FCC condition.
1383static SPCC::CondCodes FPCondCCodeToFCC(ISD::CondCode CC) {
1384 switch (CC) {
1385 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown fp condition code!");
1386 case ISD::SETEQ:
1387 case ISD::SETOEQ: return SPCC::FCC_E;
1388 case ISD::SETNE:
1389 case ISD::SETUNE: return SPCC::FCC_NE;
1390 case ISD::SETLT:
1391 case ISD::SETOLT: return SPCC::FCC_L;
1392 case ISD::SETGT:
1393 case ISD::SETOGT: return SPCC::FCC_G;
1394 case ISD::SETLE:
1395 case ISD::SETOLE: return SPCC::FCC_LE;
1396 case ISD::SETGE:
1397 case ISD::SETOGE: return SPCC::FCC_GE;
1398 case ISD::SETULT: return SPCC::FCC_UL;
1399 case ISD::SETULE: return SPCC::FCC_ULE;
1400 case ISD::SETUGT: return SPCC::FCC_UG;
1401 case ISD::SETUGE: return SPCC::FCC_UGE;
1402 case ISD::SETUO: return SPCC::FCC_U;
1403 case ISD::SETO: return SPCC::FCC_O;
1404 case ISD::SETONE: return SPCC::FCC_LG;
1405 case ISD::SETUEQ: return SPCC::FCC_UE;
1406 }
1407}
1408
1409SparcTargetLowering::SparcTargetLowering(const TargetMachine &TM,
1410 const SparcSubtarget &STI)
1411 : TargetLowering(TM), Subtarget(&STI) {
1412 MVT PtrVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(8 * TM.getPointerSize(0));
1413
1414 // Instructions which use registers as conditionals examine all the
1415 // bits (as does the pseudo SELECT_CC expansion). I don't think it
1416 // matters much whether it's ZeroOrOneBooleanContent, or
1417 // ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent, so, arbitrarily choose the
1418 // former.
1419 setBooleanContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
1420 setBooleanVectorContents(ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
1421
1422 // Set up the register classes.
1423 addRegisterClass(MVT::i32, &SP::IntRegsRegClass);
1424 if (!Subtarget->useSoftFloat()) {
1425 addRegisterClass(MVT::f32, &SP::FPRegsRegClass);
1426 addRegisterClass(MVT::f64, &SP::DFPRegsRegClass);
1427 addRegisterClass(MVT::f128, &SP::QFPRegsRegClass);
1428 }
1429 if (Subtarget->is64Bit()) {
1430 addRegisterClass(MVT::i64, &SP::I64RegsRegClass);
1431 } else {
1432 // On 32bit sparc, we define a double-register 32bit register
1433 // class, as well. This is modeled in LLVM as a 2-vector of i32.
1434 addRegisterClass(MVT::v2i32, &SP::IntPairRegClass);
1435
1436 // ...but almost all operations must be expanded, so set that as
1437 // the default.
1438 for (unsigned Op = 0; Op < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END; ++Op) {
1439 setOperationAction(Op, MVT::v2i32, Expand);
1440 }
1441 // Truncating/extending stores/loads are also not supported.
1442 for (MVT VT : MVT::integer_vector_valuetypes()) {
1443 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::v2i32, Expand);
1444 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::v2i32, Expand);
1445 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::v2i32, Expand);
1446
1447 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, MVT::v2i32, VT, Expand);
1448 setLoadExtAction(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, MVT::v2i32, VT, Expand);
1449 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, MVT::v2i32, VT, Expand);
1450
1451 setTruncStoreAction(VT, MVT::v2i32, Expand);
1452 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::v2i32, VT, Expand);
1453 }
1454 // However, load and store *are* legal.
1455 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::v2i32, Legal);
1456 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, MVT::v2i32, Legal);
1457 setOperationAction(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, MVT::v2i32, Legal);
1458 setOperationAction(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, MVT::v2i32, Legal);
1459
1460 // And we need to promote i64 loads/stores into vector load/store
1461 setOperationAction(ISD::LOAD, MVT::i64, Custom);
1462 setOperationAction(ISD::STORE, MVT::i64, Custom);
1463
1464 // Sadly, this doesn't work:
1465 // AddPromotedToType(ISD::LOAD, MVT::i64, MVT::v2i32);
1466 // AddPromotedToType(ISD::STORE, MVT::i64, MVT::v2i32);
1467 }
1468
1469 // Turn FP extload into load/fpextend
1470 for (MVT VT : MVT::fp_valuetypes()) {
1471 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::f32, Expand);
1472 setLoadExtAction(ISD::EXTLOAD, VT, MVT::f64, Expand);
1473 }
1474
1475 // Sparc doesn't have i1 sign extending load
1476 for (MVT VT : MVT::integer_valuetypes())
1477 setLoadExtAction(ISD::SEXTLOAD, VT, MVT::i1, Promote);
1478
1479 // Turn FP truncstore into trunc + store.
1480 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f64, MVT::f32, Expand);
1481 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f128, MVT::f32, Expand);
1482 setTruncStoreAction(MVT::f128, MVT::f64, Expand);
1483
1484 // Custom legalize GlobalAddress nodes into LO/HI parts.
1485 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalAddress, PtrVT, Custom);
1486 setOperationAction(ISD::GlobalTLSAddress, PtrVT, Custom);
1487 setOperationAction(ISD::ConstantPool, PtrVT, Custom);
1488 setOperationAction(ISD::BlockAddress, PtrVT, Custom);
1489
1490 // Sparc doesn't have sext_inreg, replace them with shl/sra
1491 setOperationAction(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, MVT::i16, Expand);
1492 setOperationAction(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, MVT::i8 , Expand);
1493 setOperationAction(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, MVT::i1 , Expand);
1494
1495 // Sparc has no REM or DIVREM operations.
1496 setOperationAction(ISD::UREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
1497 setOperationAction(ISD::SREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
1498 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
1499 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i32, Expand);
1500
1501 // ... nor does SparcV9.
1502 if (Subtarget->is64Bit()) {
1503 setOperationAction(ISD::UREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
1504 setOperationAction(ISD::SREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
1505 setOperationAction(ISD::SDIVREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
1506 setOperationAction(ISD::UDIVREM, MVT::i64, Expand);
1507 }
1508
1509 // Custom expand fp<->sint
1510 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, MVT::i32, Custom);
1511 setOperationAction(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, MVT::i32, Custom);
1512 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, MVT::i64, Custom);
1513 setOperationAction(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, MVT::i64, Custom);
1514
1515 // Custom Expand fp<->uint
1516 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, MVT::i32, Custom);
1517 setOperationAction(ISD::UINT_TO_FP, MVT::i32, Custom);
1518 setOperationAction(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, MVT::i64, Custom);
1519 setOperationAction(ISD::UINT_TO_FP, MVT::i64, Custom);
1520
1521 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::f32, Expand);
1522 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::i32, Expand);
1523
1524 // Sparc has no select or setcc: expand to SELECT_CC.
1525 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i32, Expand);
1526 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f32, Expand);
1527 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f64, Expand);
1528 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::f128, Expand);
1529
1530 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::i32, Expand);
1531 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f32, Expand);
1532 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f64, Expand);
1533 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::f128, Expand);
1534
1535 // Sparc doesn't have BRCOND either, it has BR_CC.
1536 setOperationAction(ISD::BRCOND, MVT::Other, Expand);
1537 setOperationAction(ISD::BRIND, MVT::Other, Expand);
1538 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_JT, MVT::Other, Expand);
1539 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::i32, Custom);
1540 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f32, Custom);
1541 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f64, Custom);
1542 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::f128, Custom);
1543
1544 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::i32, Custom);
1545 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f32, Custom);
1546 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f64, Custom);
1547 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::f128, Custom);
1548
1549 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDC, MVT::i32, Custom);
1550 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDE, MVT::i32, Custom);
1551 setOperationAction(ISD::SUBC, MVT::i32, Custom);
1552 setOperationAction(ISD::SUBE, MVT::i32, Custom);
1553
1554 if (Subtarget->is64Bit()) {
1555 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDC, MVT::i64, Custom);
1556 setOperationAction(ISD::ADDE, MVT::i64, Custom);
1557 setOperationAction(ISD::SUBC, MVT::i64, Custom);
1558 setOperationAction(ISD::SUBE, MVT::i64, Custom);
1559 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::f64, Expand);
1560 setOperationAction(ISD::BITCAST, MVT::i64, Expand);
1561 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT, MVT::i64, Expand);
1562 setOperationAction(ISD::SETCC, MVT::i64, Expand);
1563 setOperationAction(ISD::BR_CC, MVT::i64, Custom);
1564 setOperationAction(ISD::SELECT_CC, MVT::i64, Custom);
1565
1566 setOperationAction(ISD::CTPOP, MVT::i64,
1567 Subtarget->usePopc() ? Legal : Expand);
1568 setOperationAction(ISD::CTTZ , MVT::i64, Expand);
1569 setOperationAction(ISD::CTLZ , MVT::i64, Expand);
1570 setOperationAction(ISD::BSWAP, MVT::i64, Expand);
1571 setOperationAction(ISD::ROTL , MVT::i64, Expand);
1572 setOperationAction(ISD::ROTR , MVT::i64, Expand);
1573 setOperationAction(ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC, MVT::i64, Custom);
1574 }
1575
1576 // ATOMICs.
1577 // Atomics are supported on SparcV9. 32-bit atomics are also
1578 // supported by some Leon SparcV8 variants. Otherwise, atomics
1579 // are unsupported.
1580 if (Subtarget->isV9())
1581 setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(64);
1582 else if (Subtarget->hasLeonCasa())
1583 setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(32);
1584 else
1585 setMaxAtomicSizeInBitsSupported(0);
1586
1587 setMinCmpXchgSizeInBits(32);
1588
1589 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, MVT::i32, Legal);
1590
1591 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE, MVT::Other, Legal);
1592
1593 // Custom Lower Atomic LOAD/STORE
1594 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD, MVT::i32, Custom);
1595 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_STORE, MVT::i32, Custom);
1596
1597 if (Subtarget->is64Bit()) {
1598 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, MVT::i64, Legal);
1599 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, MVT::i64, Legal);
1600 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD, MVT::i64, Custom);
1601 setOperationAction(ISD::ATOMIC_STORE, MVT::i64, Custom);
1602 }
1603
1604 if (!Subtarget->is64Bit()) {
1605 // These libcalls are not available in 32-bit.
1606 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SHL_I128, nullptr);
1607 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SRL_I128, nullptr);
1608 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SRA_I128, nullptr);
1609 }
1610
1611 if (!Subtarget->isV9()) {
1612 // SparcV8 does not have FNEGD and FABSD.
1613 setOperationAction(ISD::FNEG, MVT::f64, Custom);
1614 setOperationAction(ISD::FABS, MVT::f64, Custom);
1615 }
1616
1617 setOperationAction(ISD::FSIN , MVT::f128, Expand);
1618 setOperationAction(ISD::FCOS , MVT::f128, Expand);
1619 setOperationAction(ISD::FSINCOS, MVT::f128, Expand);
1620 setOperationAction(ISD::FREM , MVT::f128, Expand);

1853/// isMaskedValueZeroForTargetNode - Return true if 'Op & Mask' is known to
1854/// be zero. Op is expected to be a target specific node. Used by DAG
1855/// combiner.
1856void SparcTargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetNode
1857 (const SDValue Op,
1858 KnownBits &Known,
1859 const APInt &DemandedElts,
1860 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
1861 unsigned Depth) const {
1862 KnownBits Known2;
1863 Known.resetAll();
1864
1865 switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
1866 default: break;
1867 case SPISD::SELECT_ICC:
1868 case SPISD::SELECT_XCC:
1869 case SPISD::SELECT_FCC:
1870 Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), Depth + 1);
1871 Known2 = DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), Depth + 1);
1872
1873 // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
1874 Known.One &= Known2.One;
1875 Known.Zero &= Known2.Zero;
1876 break;
1877 }
1878}
1879
1880// Look at LHS/RHS/CC and see if they are a lowered setcc instruction. If so
1881// set LHS/RHS and SPCC to the LHS/RHS of the setcc and SPCC to the condition.
1882static void LookThroughSetCC(SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS,
1883 ISD::CondCode CC, unsigned &SPCC) {
1884 if (isNullConstant(RHS) &&
1885 CC == ISD::SETNE &&
1886 (((LHS.getOpcode() == SPISD::SELECT_ICC ||
1887 LHS.getOpcode() == SPISD::SELECT_XCC) &&
1888 LHS.getOperand(3).getOpcode() == SPISD::CMPICC) ||
1889 (LHS.getOpcode() == SPISD::SELECT_FCC &&
1890 LHS.getOperand(3).getOpcode() == SPISD::CMPFCC)) &&
1891 isOneConstant(LHS.getOperand(0)) &&
1892 isNullConstant(LHS.getOperand(1))) {
1893 SDValue CMPCC = LHS.getOperand(3);
1894 SPCC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->getZExtValue();
1895 LHS = CMPCC.getOperand(0);
1896 RHS = CMPCC.getOperand(1);
1897 }
1898}

1900// Convert to a target node and set target flags.
1901SDValue SparcTargetLowering::withTargetFlags(SDValue Op, unsigned TF,
1902 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1903 if (const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op))
1904 return DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(),
1905 SDLoc(GA),
1906 GA->getValueType(0),
1907 GA->getOffset(), TF);
1908
1909 if (const ConstantPoolSDNode *CP = dyn_cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(Op))
1910 return DAG.getTargetConstantPool(CP->getConstVal(),
1911 CP->getValueType(0),
1912 CP->getAlignment(),
1913 CP->getOffset(), TF);
1914
1915 if (const BlockAddressSDNode *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddressSDNode>(Op))
1916 return DAG.getTargetBlockAddress(BA->getBlockAddress(),
1917 Op.getValueType(),
1918 0,
1919 TF);
1920
1921 if (const ExternalSymbolSDNode *ES = dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Op))
1922 return DAG.getTargetExternalSymbol(ES->getSymbol(),
1923 ES->getValueType(0), TF);
1924
1925 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled address SDNode");
1926}
1927
1928// Split Op into high and low parts according to HiTF and LoTF.
1929// Return an ADD node combining the parts.
1930SDValue SparcTargetLowering::makeHiLoPair(SDValue Op,
1931 unsigned HiTF, unsigned LoTF,
1932 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1933 SDLoc DL(Op);
1934 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
1935 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Hi, DL, VT, withTargetFlags(Op, HiTF, DAG));
1936 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Lo, DL, VT, withTargetFlags(Op, LoTF, DAG));
1937 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Hi, Lo);
1938}
1939
1940// Build SDNodes for producing an address from a GlobalAddress, ConstantPool,
1941// or ExternalSymbol SDNode.
1942SDValue SparcTargetLowering::makeAddress(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1943 SDLoc DL(Op);
1944 EVT VT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1945
1946 // Handle PIC mode first. SPARC needs a got load for every variable!
1947 if (isPositionIndependent()) {
1948 const Module *M = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getParent();
1949 PICLevel::Level picLevel = M->getPICLevel();
1950 SDValue Idx;
1951
1952 if (picLevel == PICLevel::SmallPIC) {
1953 // This is the pic13 code model, the GOT is known to be smaller than 8KiB.
1954 Idx = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Lo, DL, Op.getValueType(),
1955 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT13, DAG));
1956 } else {
1957 // This is the pic32 code model, the GOT is known to be smaller than 4GB.
1958 Idx = makeHiLoPair(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT22,
1959 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_GOT10, DAG);
1960 }
1961
1962 SDValue GlobalBase = DAG.getNode(SPISD::GLOBAL_BASE_REG, DL, VT);
1963 SDValue AbsAddr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, GlobalBase, Idx);
1964 // GLOBAL_BASE_REG codegen'ed with call. Inform MFI that this
1965 // function has calls.
1966 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
1967 MFI.setHasCalls(true);
1968 return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), AbsAddr,
1969 MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction()));
1970 }
1971
1972 // This is one of the absolute code models.
1973 switch(getTargetMachine().getCodeModel()) {
1974 default:
1975 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported absolute code model");
1976 case CodeModel::Small:
1977 // abs32.
1978 return makeHiLoPair(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI,
1979 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO, DAG);
1980 case CodeModel::Medium: {
1981 // abs44.
1982 SDValue H44 = makeHiLoPair(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_H44,
1983 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_M44, DAG);
1984 H44 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, H44, DAG.getConstant(12, DL, MVT::i32));
1985 SDValue L44 = withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_L44, DAG);
1986 L44 = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Lo, DL, VT, L44);
1987 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, H44, L44);
1988 }
1989 case CodeModel::Large: {
1990 // abs64.
1991 SDValue Hi = makeHiLoPair(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HH,
1992 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HM, DAG);
1993 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Hi, DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i32));
1994 SDValue Lo = makeHiLoPair(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_HI,
1995 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_LO, DAG);
1996 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Hi, Lo);
1997 }
1998 }
1999}

2015
2016SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerGlobalTLSAddress(SDValue Op,
2017 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2018
2019 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
2020 if (DAG.getTarget().useEmulatedTLS())
2021 return LowerToTLSEmulatedModel(GA, DAG);
2022
2023 SDLoc DL(GA);
2024 const GlobalValue *GV = GA->getGlobal();
2025 EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2026
2027 TLSModel::Model model = getTargetMachine().getTLSModel(GV);
2028
2029 if (model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic || model == TLSModel::LocalDynamic) {
2030 unsigned HiTF = ((model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic)
2031 ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_HI22
2032 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_HI22);
2033 unsigned LoTF = ((model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic)
2034 ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_LO10
2035 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_LO10);
2036 unsigned addTF = ((model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic)
2037 ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_ADD
2038 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_ADD);
2039 unsigned callTF = ((model == TLSModel::GeneralDynamic)
2040 ? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_GD_CALL
2041 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDM_CALL);
2042
2043 SDValue HiLo = makeHiLoPair(Op, HiTF, LoTF, DAG);
2044 SDValue Base = DAG.getNode(SPISD::GLOBAL_BASE_REG, DL, PtrVT);
2045 SDValue Argument = DAG.getNode(SPISD::TLS_ADD, DL, PtrVT, Base, HiLo,
2046 withTargetFlags(Op, addTF, DAG));
2047
2048 SDValue Chain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2049 SDValue InFlag;
2050
2051 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, 1, 0, DL);
2052 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, SP::O0, Argument, InFlag);
2053 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
2054 SDValue Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalFunctionSymbol("__tls_get_addr");
2055 SDValue Symbol = withTargetFlags(Op, callTF, DAG);
2056
2057 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
2058 const uint32_t *Mask = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()->getCallPreservedMask(
2059 DAG.getMachineFunction(), CallingConv::C);
2060 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
2061 SDValue Ops[] = {Chain,
2062 Callee,
2063 Symbol,
2064 DAG.getRegister(SP::O0, PtrVT),
2065 DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask),
2066 InFlag};
2067 Chain = DAG.getNode(SPISD::TLS_CALL, DL, NodeTys, Ops);
2068 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
2069 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, DL, true),
2070 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL, true), InFlag, DL);
2071 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
2072 SDValue Ret = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, DL, SP::O0, PtrVT, InFlag);
2073
2074 if (model != TLSModel::LocalDynamic)
2075 return Ret;
2076
2077 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Hi, DL, PtrVT,
2078 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDO_HIX22, DAG));
2079 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT,
2080 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDO_LOX10, DAG));
2081 HiLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Lo);
2082 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::TLS_ADD, DL, PtrVT, Ret, HiLo,
2083 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LDO_ADD, DAG));
2084 }
2085
2086 if (model == TLSModel::InitialExec) {
2087 unsigned ldTF = ((PtrVT == MVT::i64)? SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LDX
2088 : SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LD);
2089
2090 SDValue Base = DAG.getNode(SPISD::GLOBAL_BASE_REG, DL, PtrVT);
2091
2092 // GLOBAL_BASE_REG codegen'ed with call. Inform MFI that this
2093 // function has calls.
2094 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
2095 MFI.setHasCalls(true);
2096
2097 SDValue TGA = makeHiLoPair(Op,
2098 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_HI22,
2099 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_LO10, DAG);
2100 SDValue Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, Base, TGA);
2101 SDValue Offset = DAG.getNode(SPISD::TLS_LD,
2102 DL, PtrVT, Ptr,
2103 withTargetFlags(Op, ldTF, DAG));
2104 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::TLS_ADD, DL, PtrVT,
2105 DAG.getRegister(SP::G7, PtrVT), Offset,
2106 withTargetFlags(Op,
2107 SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_IE_ADD, DAG));
2108 }
2109
2110 assert(model == TLSModel::LocalExec);
2111 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Hi, DL, PtrVT,
2112 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LE_HIX22, DAG));
2113 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(SPISD::Lo, DL, PtrVT,
2114 withTargetFlags(Op, SparcMCExpr::VK_Sparc_TLS_LE_LOX10, DAG));
2115 SDValue Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, PtrVT, Hi, Lo);
2116
2117 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT,
2118 DAG.getRegister(SP::G7, PtrVT), Offset);
2119}
2120
2121SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerF128_LibCallArg(SDValue Chain,
2122 ArgListTy &Args, SDValue Arg,
2123 const SDLoc &DL,
2124 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2125 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
2126 EVT ArgVT = Arg.getValueType();
2127 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2128
2129 ArgListEntry Entry;
2130 Entry.Node = Arg;
2131 Entry.Ty = ArgTy;
2132
2133 if (ArgTy->isFP128Ty()) {
2134 // Create a stack object and pass the pointer to the library function.
2135 int FI = MFI.CreateStackObject(16, 8, false);
2136 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
2137 Chain = DAG.getStore(Chain, DL, Entry.Node, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo(),
2138 /* Alignment = */ 8);
2139
2140 Entry.Node = FIPtr;
2141 Entry.Ty = PointerType::getUnqual(ArgTy);
2142 }
2143 Args.push_back(Entry);
2144 return Chain;
2145}
2146
2147SDValue
2148SparcTargetLowering::LowerF128Op(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2149 const char *LibFuncName,
2150 unsigned numArgs) const {
2151
2152 ArgListTy Args;
2153
2154 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
2155 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2156
2157 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(LibFuncName);
2158 Type *RetTy = Op.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2159 Type *RetTyABI = RetTy;
2160 SDValue Chain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2161 SDValue RetPtr;
2162
2163 if (RetTy->isFP128Ty()) {
2164 // Create a Stack Object to receive the return value of type f128.
2165 ArgListEntry Entry;
2166 int RetFI = MFI.CreateStackObject(16, 8, false);
2167 RetPtr = DAG.getFrameIndex(RetFI, PtrVT);
2168 Entry.Node = RetPtr;
2169 Entry.Ty = PointerType::getUnqual(RetTy);
2170 if (!Subtarget->is64Bit())
2171 Entry.IsSRet = true;
2172 Entry.IsReturned = false;
2173 Args.push_back(Entry);
2174 RetTyABI = Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext());
2175 }
2176
2177 assert(Op->getNumOperands() >= numArgs && "Not enough operands!");
2178 for (unsigned i = 0, e = numArgs; i != e; ++i) {
2179 Chain = LowerF128_LibCallArg(Chain, Args, Op.getOperand(i), SDLoc(Op), DAG);
2180 }
2181 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2182 CLI.setDebugLoc(SDLoc(Op)).setChain(Chain)
2183 .setCallee(CallingConv::C, RetTyABI, Callee, std::move(Args));
2184
2185 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = LowerCallTo(CLI);
2186
2187 // chain is in second result.
2188 if (RetTyABI == RetTy)
2189 return CallInfo.first;
2190
2191 assert (RetTy->isFP128Ty() && "Unexpected return type!");
2192
2193 Chain = CallInfo.second;
2194
2195 // Load RetPtr to get the return value.
2196 return DAG.getLoad(Op.getValueType(), SDLoc(Op), Chain, RetPtr,
2197 MachinePointerInfo(), /* Alignment = */ 8);
2198}
2199
2200SDValue SparcTargetLowering::LowerF128Compare(SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS,
2201 unsigned &SPCC, const SDLoc &DL,
2202 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2203
2204 const char *LibCall = nullptr;
2205 bool is64Bit = Subtarget->is64Bit();
2206 switch(SPCC) {
2207 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled conditional code!");
2208 case SPCC::FCC_E : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_feq" : "_Q_feq"; break;
2209 case SPCC::FCC_NE : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_fne" : "_Q_fne"; break;
2210 case SPCC::FCC_L : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_flt" : "_Q_flt"; break;
2211 case SPCC::FCC_G : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_fgt" : "_Q_fgt"; break;
2212 case SPCC::FCC_LE : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_fle" : "_Q_fle"; break;
2213 case SPCC::FCC_GE : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_fge" : "_Q_fge"; break;
2214 case SPCC::FCC_UL :
2215 case SPCC::FCC_ULE:
2216 case SPCC::FCC_UG :
2217 case SPCC::FCC_UGE:
2218 case SPCC::FCC_U :
2219 case SPCC::FCC_O :
2220 case SPCC::FCC_LG :
2221 case SPCC::FCC_UE : LibCall = is64Bit? "_Qp_cmp" : "_Q_cmp"; break;
2222 }
2223
2224 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(LibCall);
2225 Type *RetTy = Type::getInt32Ty(*DAG.getContext());
2226 ArgListTy Args;
2227 SDValue Chain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2228 Chain = LowerF128_LibCallArg(Chain, Args, LHS, DL, DAG);
2229 Chain = LowerF128_LibCallArg(Chain, Args, RHS, DL, DAG);
2230
2231 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2232 CLI.setDebugLoc(DL).setChain(Chain)
2233 .setCallee(CallingConv::C, RetTy, Callee, std::move(Args));
2234
2235 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = LowerCallTo(CLI);
2236
2237 // result is in first, and chain is in second result.
2238 SDValue Result = CallInfo.first;
2239
2240 switch(SPCC) {
2241 default: {
2242 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Result.getValueType());
2243 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2244 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2245 }
2246 case SPCC::FCC_UL : {
2247 SDValue Mask = DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, Result.getValueType());
2248 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, Result.getValueType(), Result, Mask);
2249 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Result.getValueType());
2250 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2251 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2252 }
2253 case SPCC::FCC_ULE: {
2254 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(2, DL, Result.getValueType());
2255 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2256 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2257 }
2258 case SPCC::FCC_UG : {
2259 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, Result.getValueType());
2260 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_G;
2261 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2262 }
2263 case SPCC::FCC_UGE: {
2264 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, Result.getValueType());
2265 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2266 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2267 }
2268
2269 case SPCC::FCC_U : {
2270 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(3, DL, Result.getValueType());
2271 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_E;
2272 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2273 }
2274 case SPCC::FCC_O : {
2275 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(3, DL, Result.getValueType());
2276 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2277 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2278 }
2279 case SPCC::FCC_LG : {
2280 SDValue Mask = DAG.getTargetConstant(3, DL, Result.getValueType());
2281 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, Result.getValueType(), Result, Mask);
2282 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Result.getValueType());
2283 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_NE;
2284 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2285 }
2286 case SPCC::FCC_UE : {
2287 SDValue Mask = DAG.getTargetConstant(3, DL, Result.getValueType());
2288 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, Result.getValueType(), Result, Mask);
2289 SDValue RHS = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, Result.getValueType());
2290 SPCC = SPCC::ICC_E;
2291 return DAG.getNode(SPISD::CMPICC, DL, MVT::Glue, Result, RHS);
2292 }
2293 }
2294}

2330static SDValue LowerFP_TO_SINT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2331 const SparcTargetLowering &TLI,
2332 bool hasHardQuad) {
2333 SDLoc dl(Op);
2334 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2335 assert(VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64);
2336
2337 // Expand f128 operations to fp128 abi calls.
2338 if (Op.getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::f128
2339 && (!hasHardQuad || !TLI.isTypeLegal(VT))) {
2340 const char *libName = TLI.getLibcallName(VT == MVT::i32
2341 ? RTLIB::FPTOSINT_F128_I32
2342 : RTLIB::FPTOSINT_F128_I64);
2343 return TLI.LowerF128Op(Op, DAG, libName, 1);
2344 }
2345
2346 // Expand if the resulting type is illegal.
2347 if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VT))
2348 return SDValue();
2349
2350 // Otherwise, Convert the fp value to integer in an FP register.
2351 if (VT == MVT::i32)
2352 Op = DAG.getNode(SPISD::FTOI, dl, MVT::f32, Op.getOperand(0));
2353 else
2354 Op = DAG.getNode(SPISD::FTOX, dl, MVT::f64, Op.getOperand(0));
2355
2356 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, Op);
2357}
2358
2359static SDValue LowerSINT_TO_FP(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2360 const SparcTargetLowering &TLI,
2361 bool hasHardQuad) {
2362 SDLoc dl(Op);
2363 EVT OpVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2364 assert(OpVT == MVT::i32 || (OpVT == MVT::i64));
2365
2366 EVT floatVT = (OpVT == MVT::i32) ? MVT::f32 : MVT::f64;
2367
2368 // Expand f128 operations to fp128 ABI calls.
2369 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::f128
2370 && (!hasHardQuad || !TLI.isTypeLegal(OpVT))) {
2371 const char *libName = TLI.getLibcallName(OpVT == MVT::i32
2372 ? RTLIB::SINTTOFP_I32_F128
2373 : RTLIB::SINTTOFP_I64_F128);
2374 return TLI.LowerF128Op(Op, DAG, libName, 1);
2375 }
2376
2377 // Expand if the operand type is illegal.
2378 if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(OpVT))
2379 return SDValue();
2380
2381 // Otherwise, Convert the int value to FP in an FP register.
2382 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, floatVT, Op.getOperand(0));
2383 unsigned opcode = (OpVT == MVT::i32)? SPISD::ITOF : SPISD::XTOF;
2384 return DAG.getNode(opcode, dl, Op.getValueType(), Tmp);
2385}
